# 🌸 Flower Classification using CNN

![Python](https://img.shields.io/badge/Python-3.8+-blue?style=flat&logo=python)
![TensorFlow](https://img.shields.io/badge/TensorFlow-2.x-orange?style=flat&logo=tensorflow)
![Keras](https://img.shields.io/badge/Keras-red?style=flat&logo=keras)
![Streamlit](https://img.shields.io/badge/Streamlit-Deployed-brightgreen?style=flat&logo=streamlit)
![Accuracy](https://img.shields.io/badge/Validation%20Accuracy-92%25-success?style=flat)

A deep learning model that classifies flower species from images using a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN) — deployed as a live web app with Streamlit.

---

## 🚀 Live Demo

Upload any flower image → Get instant species prediction in your browser.

> Built with TensorFlow + Keras and deployed using Streamlit.

---

## ✨ Highlights

- **92% validation accuracy** on multi-class flower classification
- **End-to-end deployment** — not just a notebook, a working web app
- **Data augmentation** applied to reduce overfitting and improve generalization
- Real-time image upload and prediction via interactive UI

---

## 🛠️ Tech Stack

| Component | Technology |
|---|---|
| Language | Python |
| Deep Learning | TensorFlow, Keras |
| Model Architecture | CNN (Convolutional Neural Network) |
| Deployment | Streamlit |
| Image Processing | OpenCV, PIL |

---

## 📁 Project Structure

```
Flower-Classification-Model/
├── Flower_Detection.ipynb     # Model training notebook
├── Flower_Recog_Model.h5      # Saved trained model
├── app.py                     # Streamlit web app
└── README.md
```

---

## ⚙️ How to Run

```bash
# Clone the repository
git clone https://github.com/Anshu-Choudhary/Flower-Classification-Model.git
cd Flower-Classification-Model

# Install dependencies
pip install tensorflow keras streamlit opencv-python pillow numpy

# Run the app
streamlit run app.py
```

---

## 🧠 Model Details

- **Architecture:** Custom CNN with Conv2D, MaxPooling, Dropout layers
- **Input:** RGB flower images (resized to fixed dimensions)
- **Preprocessing:** Resizing, normalization, data augmentation (flipping, rotation, zoom)
- **Output:** Predicted flower species + confidence score
- **Saved Format:** `.h5` (Keras HDF5)

---

